==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: main memory
<hw>main memory</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>The
memory in a computer that holds programs and data for rapid access
during execution of a program; it usually hold the largest quantity of
rapid-access storage in a computer; -- also called
<altname>RAM</altname> (<altname>random access memory</altname>. It is
contrasted to <contr>ROM</contr>, <contr>disk data storage</contr>,
<contr>cache</contr>, <contr>registers</contr> and other forms of data
storage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mainor</ent>⟦br⟧
